TANNER'S CREEK

Noted African American artist Henry Ossawa Tanner lived in Strawberry Mansion and one day, his father took him on a ramble through E. Fairmount Park. As they entered a point near the Shuylkill, they came upon a painter working al fresco. Tanner says in his Autobiography that it was then that he realized what an artist was and he committed himself to becoming one.
